Title: US-14 OLARES VERIFY  
Author: [YOUR NAME]  
Credit: AIMPOS-Spark Visual  

INT. RESEARCH LAB - DAWN  

The lab is dimly lit, equipment humming. DR. ELARA VOSS (30s, weary but focused) stands over a bioluminescent coral sample, its glow casting eerie patterns on the walls. A satellite feed flickers on a nearby screen—three corporate ships loom on the horizon.  

DR. ELARA VOSS  
(whispering)  
If I send this... they’ll come. But if I don’t—  

A holographic projection of DR. MARCUS HALE (60s, stern) materializes.  

DR. MARCUS HALE  
(voiceover)  
You think silence protects them? It protects *you*.  

Elara clenches her fists. The coral’s glow intensifies.  

DR. ELARA VOSS  
(bitter)  
And if I stay silent, I’m no better than them.  

She grabs a transmitter, hesitates, then slams it onto the table. The screen flashes: "DATA TRANSMISSION INITIATED."  

DR. MARCUS HALE  
(voiceover)  
You’ve already lost.  

